parameters: 3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Mage Relm: There are an incredible number of books! Can I
stay overnight... I mean, can I stay for a few nights!?
Clea: Please prioritize the requests above all else.

Mage Relm: The books here have been collected specifically
for their importance in the history of the Great Rock
Castle.

Mage Relm: I have performed magical processing to ensure
that they are not damaged or soiled, but it seems like
everyone here might be able to break through it.
Priestess Sophia: Nora-chan and I will wait at the edge.
Thief Nora: Yes! I might trip and break something!

Mage Relm: The far right end is where the negotiator
Proposhi was dealt with.
Mage Relm: I can't lose either!

Mage Relm: Clea-san, I would like you to protect the
documents, please.

Clea: I doubt if I can win against both of them, but I will
handle it.

Mage Relm: As expected of a place called the [Mycos
Academy], there is a wealth of materials in a different
direction from the Magic Academy.

Mage Relm: What's interesting is that there are many
documents here that are close to biographies. Not only do
they cover magical theory, but also a lot about human
emotions.

Swift Celis: Negotiator Proposhi was a master of rhetoric
and won the establishment of the Adventurer's Guild from the
cautious King Pharmaco.
Mage Relm: I see, that might be influencing it.
Clea: How was the Adventurer's Guild established?

Swift Celis: It is said that the Imperial Army's
reconnaissance unit served as the precursor to the Guild,
with members skilled in negotiation, reconnaissance,
exploration, investigation, and combat.

Clea: There seems to be something that connects to the
current Adventurer's Guild, right?

Swift Celis: It is said that the form of accepting requests
was established by the second Guild Master, Piste.

Mage Relm: Celis-san, you really know a lot. It's like
you're a researcher from the Magic Academy...

Mage Relm: P-Please look! It's written about sending out a
Pulse!

Mage Relm: The current place name is slightly different...
but I believe it is near the village of Irini.
Clea: It matches with Opuro-san's information, doesn't it?

Swift Celis: They said that you can post requests on the
Camps bulletin board.

Mage Relm: Indeed, it's like a swift wind... Let's wake the
two of them up as well.

Clea (Celis-san's dream that she didn't tell me about that
day...)

Clea (Could it be about the whereabouts of the first Guild
Master?)
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
